Guys there is an opportunity for you to ensure that Confluence can run as a service on 64 bit Windows. All you need to do is distribute the 64 bit versions of the Tomcat binaries which can be downloaded from [Apache SVN repository|http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/tomcat/tc6.0.x/tags/TOMCAT_6_0_14/res/procrun/amd64/] (this link is for the binaries that are to be distributed with the Tomcat version for 2.10 RC1).

The procedure is simple - have a read of the comment I made in [JRA-12965|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-12965?focusedCommentId=136318&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#action_136318]. I have been running 2.9.2 on 64 bit Windows Server 2003 for several weeks now without issue and of course the beauty of this is that I have been able to allocate a significant amount of memory to the JVM (viz. 512m of PermGen memory and 4G for the heap - considering of course that I have 8GB of physical memory installed). Of course I am successfully running 2.10 on a 64 bit Windows Server 2008 staging box.

